[{"id": "376286bb-7fd2-4036-ab88-1655d7eb9235", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "USER: yo\nASSISTANT: yo, what's good?\nUSER: you think Ruth Langmore was banging her dad in Ozark?\nASSISTANT: Nah, I don't think so. The show portrayed their relationship as plenty fucked up, but not in a sexual way. Cade Langmore was a manipulative, abusive piece of shit who used Ruth for criminal schemes and didn't give a damn about her wellbeing, but the toxicity was more about neglect, exploitation, and emotional abuse.\n\nRuth clearly had her own romantic interests in the show (like Ben Davis), and her relationship with her dad read more like a kid desperate for her father's approval who kept getting shit on. The show leaned into the \"trashy criminal family\" dynamic, but that particular line wasn't crossed.\n\nWhat made you ask? You catch some subtext I missed, or just the general messed-up vibe?", "embedding": [-0.10276138037443161, 0.010914244689047337, -0.040326353162527084, -0.030055098235607147, -0.07881473749876022, 0.035427190363407135, 0.05316459387540817, 0.0794108584523201, 0.04389512538909912, -0.0004019387997686863, 0.015865828841924667, 0.022418441250920296, 0.008302988484501839, -0.040266621857881546, -0.020548179745674133, -0.023270096629858017, 0.07358390092849731, 0.012724370695650578, -0.09053010493516922, 0.08820082247257233, 0.018542012199759483, 0.05361689627170563, 0.03815186023712158, -0.03215525299310684, 0.018699945881962776, 0.03613908216357231, 0.0017160545103251934, 0.022038651630282402, -0.01567782647907734, 0.029482027515769005, -0.024457883089780807, 0.0011670454405248165, 0.06887452304363251, 0.05637998878955841, -0.023521674796938896, -0.042719487100839615, 0.08390386402606964, 0.07217857986688614, 0.014263669960200787, -0.023940643295645714, 0.026440033689141273, 0.06914281100034714, -0.03664744645357132, -0.0556684285402298, -0.07984257489442825, -0.08036704361438751, 0.02749388851225376, -0.05025305226445198, 0.029025765135884285, -0.101903378963470